-- Brait, Standard Bank, Wooltru: South African Equity Preview
-- B y   F r a n z   W i l d   a n d   G a r t h   T h e u n i s s e n
-- 2010-10-29T06:07:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-28/brait-standard-bank-sekunjalo-investments-south-african-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last close.  The  FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index  rose for the first day
in three, adding 230.74, or 0.8 percent, to 30,186.58 at the 5
p.m. close in Johannesburg.  Anglo American Plc  (AGL SJ): Copper fell 1.1 percent to
$8,251.5 a metric ton on the London Metal Exchange. Stock of
Anglo, the diversified mining company that makes up almost 10
percent of South Africa’s benchmark stock index, rose 2.50 rand,
or 0.8 percent, to 321.50 rand. Shares in larger rival  BHP
Billiton Plc  (BIL SJ) rose 6.40 rand, or 2.7 percent, to 246
rand.  Brait SA  (BAT SJ): South Africa’s largest buyout company
first-half profit rose 50 percent to 116 million rand ($16.5
million). Brait advanced 30 cents, or 1.2 percent, to 24.80
rand.  SacOil Holdings Ltd.  (SCL SJ): The oil-exploration company
with a concession in the Democratic Republic of Congo said it
posted a loss of 6.95 million rand in the six months ended Aug.
31, according to a stock-exchange statement. The company’s stock
fell 3 cents, or 1.9 percent, to 1.57 rand.  Sasol Ltd.  (SOL SJ): Oil fell as much as 0.7 percent to
$81.63 a barrel in electronic trading in New York. Stock of
Sasol, the world’s biggest maker of motor fuel from coal, rose
2.69 rand, or 0.9 percent, to 317.69 rand.  Sekunjalo Investments Ltd.  (SKJ SJ): The investment group
said earnings per share excluding one-time items for the year
through August were between 2.09 cents and 2.39 cents. Sekunjalo
jumped to its highest price since June 2009, adding 4 cents, or
11 percent, to 41 cents.  Standard Bank Group Ltd.  (SBK SJ): Africa’s biggest lender
is scheduled to hold a briefing on staff retrenchments. Standard
Bank lost 52 cents, or 0.5 percent, to 103.23 rand.  Wooltru Ltd.  (WLO SJ): The investment holding company said
it concluded the purchase of PBT Group (Pty) Ltd., Stricklands
Tetra Cape (Pty) Ltd. as well as a 51 percent stake in PBT
Insurance Technologies (Pty) Ltd., according to a stock-exchange
filing. Shares of Wooltru were unchanged at 8 cents.  Shares or American depositary receipts of the following
South African companies closed as follows:  Anglo American Plc (AAUKY US) added 1.9 percent to $23.
AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) climbed 2.9 percent to $46.44.
BHP Billiton Ltd. (BBL US) rose 3.3 percent to $71.08. DRDGold
Ltd. (DROOY US) climbed 2.5 percent to $4.91. Gold Fields Ltd.
(GFI US) advanced 2.7 percent to $15.43. Harmony Gold Mining Co.
(HMY US) added 0.3 percent to $11.28. Impala Platinum Holdings
Co. (IMPUY US) gained 0.3 percent to $27.57. Sappi Ltd. (SPP US)
lost 0.2 percent to $4.98. Sasol Ltd. (SSL US) rose 0.9 percent
to $45.39. Telkom South Africa Ltd. (TLKGY US) slumped 3.6
percent to $20.70.  To contact the reporters on this story:
